article.headline: Colgate 68, Army 58
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Kyle Roemer totaled 26 points, hitting a 3-pointer to force overtime and sinking a pair of late free throws in the extra frame to seal Colgate's 68-58 win over Army on Saturday. Roemer, who came in averaging 25 points per contest in Colgate's last three games, scored nine points for Colgate in OT. Roemer's 3 with 35 seconds left in regulation forced the extra period. Yaw Gyawu, who finished with 15 points for the Raiders (5-10, 1-0 Patriot League), scored six of those in overtime. Colgate trailed by four points at halftime, but outscored the Black Knights 26-22 in the second and 15-5 in OT. Cleveland Richard was the lone player in double figures for the Black Knights (10-5, 0-1), scoring 20 points. The Raiders have won four straight, and five of their last six, since opening the season on a nine-game losing slide.
